        {
          "key": "flags.midi-qol.OverTime",
          "mode": 2,
          "value": "turn=start,\ndamageRoll=1d6,\ndamageType=necrotic,\nlabel=Lacerated,\nchatFlavor=THIS A BIG CUT CUH,\nsaveDC=20,\nactionSave=dialog,\nrollType=skill,\nactionSave=true,\nsaveAbility=med,\nfastForwardDamage=true,",
          "priority": 20
        }
      ],
      "description": "<p><strong>Max Ranks</strong>: 100</p><hr /><p>A <strong>Lacerated</strong> creature has suffered a major wound on their body and begins to bleed profusely, the rushing blood causing the wound to grow in intensity with each passing second.</p><ul><li><p>A <strong>Lacerated</strong> creature is counted as <strong>Bleeding</strong> for the purposes of interacting with Features, Traits and Jutsu</p></li><li><p>At the beginning of a <strong>Lacerated</strong> creatures turn, they take 1d6 necrotic damage per rank of Lacerated they have.</p></li><li><p>A <strong>Lacerated</strong> creature that gains ranks of Bleeding, gains ranks of Lacerated instead.</p></li><li><p>A <strong>Lacerated</strong> creature cannot gain the benefits of a rest.</p></li><li><p>As an Action, A <strong>Lacerated</strong> creature may attempt to stop the Laceration by succeeding on a DC 20 Medicine check with a Medicine Kit.</p></li><li><p>A creature with ranks of lacerated gains one rank of laceration at the end of its turns.</p></li><li><p>A creature immune to the bleeding condition is immune to the lacerated condition.</p></li><li><p>Outside of combat, every 10-minutes a creature suffers the effects of this condition as if a turn has passed in combat.</p></li></ul>",
